High Court throws out rules introduced to stop violent criminals being transferred out of high-security jails .
Rules introduced after fugitive armed robber Michael Wheatley walked out of open jail .
He was on day release from Standford Hill prison in Kent despite a history of escapes .
But two senior judges at London's High Court have now ruled barring transfers for prisoners with a past of absconding was unlawful .
Ministers say policy is 'tearing up system as it exists at the moment'